<article id="post-260" class="post-260 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general">
	
	<header class="entry-header">
		<h1 class="entry-title">Some minor changes</h1>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Helloes.</p>
<p>As a result of various discussions <a href="http://micfic.wordpress.com/2010/08/23/new-theme-spanner/">here</a> and in meatspace, the tight 250 limit has been <em>officially</em> relaxed a little. 250 words is still the target, but between 200 and 300 is okay.<br />
Huzzah!</p>
<p>Sometimes people will want to write a longer (or shorter) story for a Theme than the limit allows.<br />
This is excellent and awesome! <img src="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><br />
The <strong>Rewrites</strong> Category has been changed to <strong>Extras</strong>. This can still be for rewrites, but also for the special extended editions, the director&#8217;s cuts, the 200 words extra footage not seen in the official theatrical release.<br />
The official Submission to a Theme should still adhere to the word limit, though.</p>
<p>Goodbyes.<br />
<img src="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	
